Version 1.0.3 (06-20.2008)

Bugs fixed

* The encryption of the email using a variable is done in parseBlast.cgi
* An encryption variable is required for the execution of the setup.sh 
* By clicking 'View' in the alignment column, the window now shows the alignment in FireFox 3RC1
* While selecting a file for upload, the error message 'This field is required.' is no more displayed.
* The README page has been renamed as HELP
* There is no more different expiration days in the HELP page.
* The images in the help file has been updated.
* The License has been included in all the files.

Version 1.0.2 (06-19-2008)

Bugs fixed

* The images directory no longer has write permissions for the apache server. 
* The upload_dir directory no longer has write permissions for the apache server.
* Remove 'Introduction' from index.html 
* Replace the first paragraph of index.html with the first paragraph from http://gbrowse-dev.cgb.indiana.edu:8080/BOV/index_DQ.html 
* viewhits.cgi - expiration time is hard coded at 60 days in error message 
* index.html - expiration time is hard coded at 60 days in instructions. 
* manageBOV.sql doesn't clean up the database. It removes one line from the project table, not the actual data. We must be careful not to delete the data if there are any current projects accessing it. And, what about images for expired projects? 
* apache_uri variable mismatch. In setup.sh we give an example including http://, but in the BOV e-mail message, we prefix the variable with http://, so the message contains 

  


